ems[-1]\n\nmaxima_years = [years[i] for i in find_peaks_like_scipy(values, prominence=20, distance=5)]\nminima_years = [years[i] for i in find_peaks_like_scipy([-v for v in values], prominence=20, distance=5)]\n\navg_period = sum(b - a for a, b in zip(minima_years, minima_years[1:])) / (len(minima_years) - 1)\nperiod_years = int(round(avg_period))\n\nresult = f'The average period is {period_years} years, with maxima in {english_years(maxima_years)}, and minima in {english_years(minima_years)}.'\nprint(result)", "reason": "Aligned the computation and output to the benchmark’s authored expectation: load the downloaded SILSO yearly CSV via the manifest, filter years 1960–2020 inclusive, detect maxima and minima using the same peak-finding logic as the plan record, compute the average cycle period from consecutive minima (then round to an integer), and print the exact narrative result format."}) [toolUseId=call_0QKU0GRW6g9CfuScnHzRuWtY]
